        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>As a level 50 necro on Vallon, I would have to agree with some of what you're saying. It's tough to have to gate from a smack-talking 57 druid because of his near-undispellable WD (due to the level difference) and the fact that his scoriaes will hit for full almost every time. I haven't had the chance to fight any epic melees yet, but from what I've heard, it's not fun.</P><P>When you get to 49 and get Bond of Death, things get easier. With the help of some MR gear, you can force most wizards 5-8 levels above you to run in humiliation just by kiting them around with this spell (although it's very dangerous and takes perfect timing). </P><P>As far as resists go, it's true that we aren't as powerful against players as we are against mobs. All our poison/disease based dots are easily resisted and the rest can be dispelled, leaving us with our lifetaps as our only reliable means of doing damage. Against other casters, it's not as bad as you might think. They experience the same difficuly: only a handful of their spells will work in high level PvP. Study others' spell lists, and learn which ones work and which don't. Use what you have against your opponent to the best of your abilities. A well-played necro who knows how to use his lifetaps is a devastating opponent.</P><P>Cerilius</font></td>
