f Nights then bye bye wizards) THEN TOUCH OF NIGHT TOUCH OF NIGHT /wave. Ok enchanters buy dot potions and dot your self, then attack them there toast i use mostly defluxes and try too get a couple dots in there easy if you dont have dot potions dot your self with the level 39 disease dot. For newbies out there you use dot on your self too cancel there suck mez ,and when fighting enchanters high mr gear is a must, so invest in Blue diamond and diamond resist gear. Fighing level 60 shamans with malo *sigh* quite tough for us, malo goes right were DMF icon is at and cancels dmf and debuffs the holy hell out you, drops  pr not too mention no more levitation  then it gets ugly for necros, with shamans that dont have malo then watch there dispelling tactics if they dispell your first dot follow it up with a dispell on them of your own, some times with druids and shamans I start dispelling them off the get go a couple times, if i have golem wands on me I stip them bare of there buffs but i hate doing that right of the get go cause then they run or gate and wasted golem wand =/. With druids and Necros make sure when fighting them you cancel your first DoT slot and if you see a necro or druid casting another dot on you cancel the next buff you have on you down the line, this way you can imeddiately annul these dots, annul or cancel magic is so little mana compared too offensive dots, with practice you can time it too were you see the opponent casting the dot on you then you can cast annul on your self so its almost instantly cancled on you. I will leave one last thing I can not stress more, watch your opponent, the wrong thing and common mistake I see novice necros do is run up on there person they are fighting and mana dump all there dots, then  all dots get dispelled and necro is LOM and has too run or they stick around tapping with there last bits of mana then get rocked , that is the worst thing you can do, we are dmg over time dealers so if the fight drags out so be it lich while you fight if it gets dispelled cast it again, one last thing here is my spell line up its for a 60 necro but you can modify too fit your level and PvP needs top slot first on down too bottom, Touch of Night, Deflux, Annul magic,Gate(or shadow step depends on how many I am taking on and if in a dungeon or out in the open), splurt, pyrocuror,vexing mordinia,quivering veil of xarn(This is also hotkeyed for fast access). Well this is the way I do it on rallos zek , were the only server were you can lose that fat item you took a week too camp, and I am constantly watching my back and checking the zone for Kill on Site. You bluebies out there you can pick your fights, for me I PvP every single day I play the game, nothing like 12 60s gating in to GD portal, casting on you at once, ummm can you say harmshield! Anyways practice hope this helps Tear it up, leave the bitching too the griefers, HOLD YOUR HEAD HIGH YOUR THE BEST CLASS IN THE GAME ! Booyea Level 60 Warlock of Rallos Zek <a href="http://www.ascendingdawn.com" target="_blank">www.ascendingdawn.com</a></P><P> </font></td>
